00:00:08.686 --> 00:00:11.468
There's this little girl in Ohio who saw the

00:00:11.468 --> 00:00:13.606
Project for Awesome video I made last year for

00:00:13.606 --> 00:00:16.154
Not Forgotten, which is an orphanage we work with in Peru

00:00:16.154 --> 00:00:18.160
and I make a video about it every December,

00:00:18.160 --> 00:00:21.167
and she saw the video and instead of just donating

00:00:21.167 --> 00:00:24.197
like we usually do, you know we see something on the internet

00:00:24.197 --> 00:00:25.851
and like oh yeah I'll click the button, or I'll whatever,

00:00:25.851 --> 00:00:27.330
I'll.. couple of bucks here, whatever.

00:00:27.330 --> 00:00:29.539
She actually did something about it.

00:00:29.539 --> 00:00:33.344
Like so she saw it and she decided to take action on her own.

00:00:33.344 --> 00:00:35.459
For something called her compassion project.

00:00:35.459 --> 00:00:38.139
I don't know what that is, but it's pretty amazing.

00:00:38.139 --> 00:00:42.499
So what I'd like to do is show you Savannah's video,

00:00:42.499 --> 00:00:44.044
her dad gave me permission to do that,

00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:48.630
