00:00:49.871 --> 00:00:52.548
Hi, my name is Savannah,

00:00:52.548 --> 00:00:54.872
and I'm in second grade.

00:00:54.872 --> 00:00:58.370
Each kid in my class was assigned a compassion project

00:00:58.370 --> 00:01:00.251
and here's mine.

00:01:01.261 --> 00:01:05.744
My dad and I watch a YouTube channel called Smarter Every Day.

00:01:07.774 --> 00:01:12.925
Through that we learned about an organization called Not Forgotten.

00:01:15.399 --> 00:01:20.451
Not Forgotten is building an orphanage in Peru to help boys

00:01:20.451 --> 00:01:22.352
who have been abandoned.

00:01:22.731 --> 00:01:26.659
Peru is in South America.

00:01:27.018 --> 00:01:31.197
When I heard about this, I told my dad we needed to do something.

00:01:31.399 --> 00:01:34.742
I decided to try and raise money to help them

00:01:34.742 --> 00:01:38.649
build an orphanage. My goal was $100.

00:01:40.934 --> 00:01:45.859
During christmas break I talked to lots of people about Not Forgotten

00:01:45.859 --> 00:01:48.609
and asked them to help me meet my goal.

00:01:49.462 --> 00:01:51.972
[music]

00:02:00.628 --> 00:02:06.134
Everyone was VERY generous. I raised four times my original goal.

00:02:06.870 --> 00:02:10.468
Together we raised $469.

00:02:12.170 --> 00:02:15.534
I was so excited to get home to make the donation.

00:02:15.534 --> 00:02:18.220
This will make a big difference for the boys in Peru.

00:02:18.220 --> 00:02:20.589
It might even save a boy's life.

00:02:24.247 --> 00:02:28.929
Thank you so much to everyone who helped me meet my goal.

00:02:32.823 --> 00:02:37.658
Right now we are in Iquitos Peru, you can see by the motor cars,

00:02:37.658 --> 00:02:40.532
and we're gonna use the money that Savannah came up with

00:02:40.532 --> 00:02:42.230
which was $1400 soles,

00:02:42.230 --> 00:02:44.612
and we're gonna use it for the orphans.

00:02:44.618 --> 00:02:46.053
It's pretty awesome.

00:02:46.829 --> 00:02:48.685
We're gonna buy beds.

00:02:56.049 --> 00:02:57.353
(Destin) What you got?

00:02:57.353 --> 00:03:05.036
- So, turns out 1450 soles pay for those 5 mattresses for that first room.

00:03:05.036 --> 00:03:08.416
Savannah that's the exact amount of money you raised for us last year

00:03:08.416 --> 00:03:10.399
so we're gonna go ahead and get these mattresses,

00:03:10.399 --> 00:03:13.590
take them out to our first house the boys are gonna use to sleep in.

00:03:13.590 --> 00:03:14.454
- Sweet.

00:03:14.454 --> 00:03:15.135
- Mucho gracias.

00:03:15.135 --> 00:03:15.812
- Yeah.

00:03:15.812 --> 00:03:17.266
Savannah, this is awesome.

00:03:17.266 --> 00:03:20.130
